<title>SWEDEN: Atlas Copco finalises Thome-Crepelle buy.</title>
<headline>Atlas Copco finalises Thome-Crepelle buy.</headline>
<dateline>STOCKHOLM 1997-05-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>Swedish engineering concern Atlas Copco said on Friday it had finalised its acquisition of French compressor group Thome-Crepelle.</p>
<p>It bought the group from Compagnie Fives-Lille.  </p>
<p>Atlas and Fives-Lille reached a preliminary agreement on March 5 which was subject to necessary approvals and the reaching of a mutually acceptable purchase agreement.</p>
<p>The company did not disclose the purchase price.</p>
<p>Thome-Crepelle of Lille has about 200 employees and its 1996 sales amounted to 196 million francs.</p>
<p>Atlas Copco previously said it planned to take the company over before the end of the second quarter.</p>
<p>-- Birgitta Forsberg, Stockholm newsroom +46-8-700 1017</p>
